{
  "doc_id": "38239",
  "text": "The prospective observational study on comorbidities and virologic outcome among patients on ART in rural Lesotho was conducted in 10 rural facilities in 2 districts in Lesotho, Southern Africa (www.clinicaltrials.gov; NCT02126696). All facilities (2 hospitals and 8 health centers) provide nurse-based HIV care for approximately 6000 patients on ART, including about 400 children. The study assessed viral suppression among patients on ART in Lesotho, who did not have access to VL testing before the study. Results from a cross-sectional first-time VL measurement among children have been published previously. [CITATION_1] In this study, we report the 18-month follow-up for those children who had unsuppressed VL at the initial time point.",
  "correct_citation": {
